title: PPPP’s Agha Saraj Khan Durrani wins PS- 9 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Agha Saraj Khan Durrani has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-9,Shikarpur- III by securing 63,760 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Rushd-ullah Shah of Jamiat Ulmah–e–Islam Pakistan (JIP), who bagged votes 25,634.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 39.04 %.
